text: Isa Rahunen (born 16 April 1993) is a Finnish former ice hockey player who played with KalPa Kuopio (2006-2013), Oulun Kärpät (2013-2020) and the Finnish national team.2019 IIHF Women's World Championship roster While representing Finland in international competition she won a silver medal at the 2019 IIHF Women's World Championship and bronze medals at the 2018 Winter Olympic Games and the 2017 IIHF Women's World Championship.
